@nikolasibalic I'm not sure whether this is the same problem here, but I have also faced the pickle problem between Python2 and Python3 in another project recently.  The cause was that some classes were define as so-called old-style classes
```python
class Something:
```
These are incompatible with Python3.  In Python3 all classes are new-style classes.  You can obtain new-style classes in Python2 as well by simply deriving them from `object`.
```python
class Something(object):
```
This syntax works in Python2 and Python3.  You might want to give it a shot.

